			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Nifty tricks for 65 LDoN. (Easy and hard)<a name="53008"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 21 04 11:14 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've decided to post a big list of tips and tricks, and plan on editting in any ones I learn or are posted that I didn't know.  Some of these are fairly commonly known, and some aren't.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Both (Can be useful in either difficulty):
<br />

<br />
- They've semi-recently added in the ability to cycle through nearest NPC's.  Set a hotkey up for it, and you can easily mez 4 mobs at once (assuming no resists).  What's even better, is that while mezzing the 4 mobs, you can still melee!  Just be a little bit careful with it, it's range IS fairly small and sometimes doesn't pick up mobs behind you.  This trick can do all sorts of amazing things for you.  It can even be used in places like Guk etc. to make sure there are no more adds around!
<br />

<br />
-We all know the toggle last 2 targets command, but I should say it anyways. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
-Bellow can break bitten victims / creaking crates / whatever from outside of the bad effects radius (ie, traps don't hit you, spawned bugs or whatever don't aggro, etc.).  If you're on a slaughter or your tank wants a pet, it can be fairly beneficial to knock those things out.   Especially if you're doing an AE group.
<br />

<br />
-Maps make things so much easier.  Get a map!
<br />

<br />
- Get the FT augments!  With 1900 points you can get FT5!  (FT2 aug chest only in EF - 510.  FT2 aug other slots - 1150 in EF.  340 in MMC for an FT1.)  There are even more augs then this, too, like in Guk or an FT1 aug that's type 7.... or.. or.. or.. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
- This is fairly obvious, but if you have rangers in your group with archery aa's, try to avoid the hallways and stick to the bigger rooms.  Key word - try.  No rules set in stone, etc.  You wouldn't believe how many rangers thanked me because they're not used to being able to use archery for most of the adventure. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
-If you have a different haster, don't worry about letting WoZ slide (while fighting casters).  Rizl will add more dps, PoV will save more mana for the healer, and marr makes every one happy.  
<br />

<br />
-Stay out of LoS when you get back to group.  Casters can slow things down quite a bit when they stand at the back of a hallway and try to nuke through your PoV.
<br />

<br />
- Using chainmezz can save your group a lot of time.  If you hit mez (assuming you have the 65 version) on casters right as you leave to pull more, you may interrupt gate, CHeal, or a ton of other stuff.  In Ruj its use is less effective (the dungeons are a lot bigger) but can still save lots of hiney.
<br />

<br />
Easy:
<br />

<br />
-Call of the Banshee works here!  You need to find a charmable mob, and have about 70/30 chance of it being charmable (others are too high).  These hit for 364 max and are a nice little addition to dps.  Ask for a malos or tash if a mage / shaman / chanter are in group (or both) and till it to sit back with the group when you go off to pull.  In a lot of dungeons, you won't pull anyways (the rush strategy, happens lots of times in advs).
<br />

<br />
EDIT::  I have recently discovered that ratio is off per different dungeons.  Tak is very hard to find a charmable mob, while Ruj is very easy.  I haven't done enough testing in the others yet.
<br />

<br />
-With your charmed pet, RoT, and dots, you can almost solo named.  (I have also solo'd multiple normal mobs as we were moving too fast and some one takes a wrong turn and gets agro while I was pulling something else)  I've personally sent it in and did the RoT + Angstlich + dots and got the named to less then 50% with my pet still over 80 before the other group members decided to help (we were just fooling around, most of them were time geared.  I was dared to try to solo it with 'Sparky.')
<br />

<br />
-For charms, make sure you have the right model.  Mini-chart below.  The name doesn't matter, the type doesn't matter.  It just has to have that model type.
<br />
Guk - Eyes (I think, haven't personally verified this)
<br />
Ruj - Wolves
<br />
Mira - Flying Monkeys
<br />
Tak - Stonegrabbers
<br />
MMC  - Mummies
<br />

<br />
- As I mentioned earlier, if your group is well equipped don't bother pulling.  Just charge through and do as much dps as possible, although you may still want to pull when dealing with crowded rooms / named.
<br />

<br />
High Risks! :
<br />
- With VoTS, epic, and SM2 I can pull my oogliness (charisma 154) to 279 (using 59 song).  With JF1, I rarely get resists (crit or otherwise) when dealing with hard risk lulling.  Per hard, I get maybe 2 or 3 crit resists max, although normal resists can vary greatly.  It is unreliable and I do use other methods, but a lot of people downplay just how useful it is.  
<br />

<br />
- We all know the mez, let other mobs come, fade at camp trick.
<br />

<br />
-But how many of us know the mez, see if other mobs come, if none come use bellow to break mez trick?  (I learned that here, thanks who ever said it.  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> )
<br />

<br />
-Bind sight is very useful for corners.  I often don't have time to check, but if your map tells you there could be a ton of mobs there and there's one standing at the door so you can't check, it's better safe then sorry.   Or, just use fade if you get a ton of agro messages.  I prefer to play conservative with my mana though. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
-Leave some room for pulling.  That way, if you get 2, it won't kill any one - you can mezz it away from the camp and still do the singing stuff and melee, and just use toggle to hit it again and mez it away from camp.  Then pop bellow on it when the other mob's dead and you've got yourself another apparent single pull<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />.
<br />

<br />
- You can do CC just fine if you have a shaman or a mage.  Just ask that all adds be malos'd and your mezz will stick so often that your group won't like chanters unless they charm ;).</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
