			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Nifty tricks for 65 LDoN. (Easy and hard)<a name="57233"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 18 04 1:04 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>This guide is awesome!  Here are a few more:
<br />

<br />
Snare a mob you aren't sure about, instead of mez/bellow, to see if any of it's friends will agro you.
<br />

<br />
If you have a pesky caster mob, run back to your group, and hide around a corner.  If you have Health of Target's Target Leaderhip AA, you can see when the mob agros the tank.  Also, for mobs you are SURE will be casters, without adds, you can start your agro song (HoS), run out of LoS, and keep out of sight of it, so it won't waste time casting on you.
<br />

<br />
Sneak is great for getting into rooms you aren't sure about.  Just make sure it actually worked.
<br />

<br />
If you have a crappy monitor like I do, turning your automap faded level to about 35% can help you see in dark dungeons, like Lguk and MM.
<br />

<br />
Do not try this at home, kids: (or with an enchanter in group).  When I get an add, or pull too early, I offtank the mob, giving me time to debuff it and I turn off attack (or toggle back to main mob) JUST before my mez lands.  This keeps it from agroing clerics/rogues and the like.  Requires some practice, but can be done.
<br />

<br />
On a high risk, if you get 3 mobs, and have enough room between them and the camp, mez 1 on the way, mez another, and have the tank kill the third.  This gives you time to spread out your incoming mobs, because it's much easier to handle them 1 at a time.
<br />

<br />
Before accepting a high risk adventure, make sure the tank is decent.  Bazaar gear/no defensive AA will probably not do too well if there are any adds.
<br />

<br />
If tanking/pulling a LDON, use DoTs/HoS/RoT to pull, and have plenty of room between the group and the mobs you pull, so you can build agro.  Make sure DPS/Debuffers in the group know not to do anything BEFORE you hit your &lt;assist me now with %t&gt; button.  Learn when to use this button.
<br />

<br />
If you die, and really need mana to pull, try to get a normal rez, loot your gear except for 1 piece, and see if cleric can Divine Rez you.  This will restore your mana to 100%, and has made the difference in several groups I've been in.
<br />

<br />
Make your rules clear before entering dungeon -- I have a hotbutton that looks something like this (I target the MA):
<br />

<br />
Ldonrulz
<br />
/g Rules: /assist %t.  Do not assist me, I change target to mez.  Only move up when I say it's safe.
<br />
/tt /assist tangerine when I hit my TAG macro, and tag.
<br />

<br />
Singing steel boots are helpful in Guk dungeons, as you can levitate over pits and things that would slow you down.
<br />

<br />
Dummy buffs are a good idea as a puller.  VoTS, Illusion mask, and SS boots are good sources of dummy buffs, so you don't lose virtue, etc.
<br />

<br />
That's all I can think of for now, maybe more later -- Enjoy!</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
