				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Nifty tricks for 65 LDoN. (Easy and hard)<a name="57314"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 18 04 11:05 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Great tips!
<br />

<br />
When doing highrisk or normals my lineup doesnt change much at all.
<br />

<br />
slots 1-4 is generally composed of my normal twist. Zek/marr/muse/veeshan
<br />

<br />
Slot 5 is my pull song, usually have a debuff or dispell or slow.
<br />

<br />
Slot 6 is for kazumis in highrisk, never know when you need a few seconds to get everyone zoned in one piece. In normals I will put a second pull song here, generally a slow(with debuff in slot 5).
<br />

<br />
Slot7 is lull (SSoQ)
<br />

<br />
Slot8 is mezz(lullaby of Morrel).
<br />

<br />
If I am only slower in highrisk(has happened), Muse is replaced with RoT. If I'm only slower in Normal, Ill pull with slow, if it lands fine, if it doesnt Ill retry when it pops again, not too worried about slowing in normals anymore.
<br />

<br />
I generally don't keep a snare up in highrisk, since I pull from far away, if it gets to be a problem slots 5-6 and muse are always expendable.
<br />

<br />
My tips for highrisk LDoNs:
<br />

<br />
ALWAYS have a buffer room or two and if you can, pull from as far away as you can. This way, when you screw up or something unexpected occurs, you have room to kite around and get things under control.
<br />

<br />
Don't be afraid to utilize your proximity to the zone-out when breaking the entrance to a crowded dungeon where theres not any room to kite adds or fade.
<br />

<br />
Deftdance will save your life, but only once. So use it as sparingly as possible. If you pull more than 3, dont deftdance, kite or zone or fade to split them. Use deftdance to absorb damage from a small crowd of mobs that you know you will be able to control, why deftdance against 6 mobs if your group will just have to zone them anyway. Use kazumis when you need to retreat.
<br />

<br />
Watch for traps. Especially stun traps in Nro. In normals they are merely a nuisance, in highrisk, a stun for a few seconds while pulling will get you killed very quickly.
<br />
</span></td>
