				<td colspan="2"><span>Level 65 Bard here, with 123 AA's who pretty much exclusively does LDoN's both normal and Hard.  No uber gear, unless you include LDoN gear as uber.
<br />

<br />

<br />
What do I do on hards?
<br />

<br />
Get a charisma buff, takes me to about 230 or so, plenty.
<br />

<br />
Some say dont lull ... bah ... pick a blue con mob, and pac it.  It may resist ... and again ... but keep trying<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />  If that fails..
<br />

<br />
Fade ... and split the pull or bring back 2-3 to camp.
<br />

<br />
BUT ... the most important thing to consistently winning on hards is ... Flowing Thought and Mental Clarity.
<br />

<br />
Between the two I regen 13 a tick standing, and 14 a tick sitting.
<br />

<br />
Between pac'ing and fading and sometimes using proximity aggro, I usually dont go below half mana.
<br />

<br />
I use Fade, and often, way more than I need to.  There is no real reason to be a show off.  Get the mission done, and dont train the group.
<br />

<br />
My record on hards is:  29-5.
<br />

<br />
Aalamina Superstarr
<br />
65 Maestro
<br />
Saryrn.</span></td>
